    "created_at": "2012-06-29T21:33:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-06-29T21:36:25Z",
    "body": "I was surprised to learn that `vec::append*()` are marked pure while effectively altering the lhs (after overtaking ownership).\nThat's more like D's \"weak purity\" than Haskell's purity: http://leonardo-m.livejournal.com/99194.html\n",
